1
00:01:14,959 --> 00:01:15,760
Hello, President Su.

2
00:01:16,519 --> 00:01:17,159
Director Shen.

3
00:01:17,480 --> 00:01:18,400
Where are you?

4
00:01:18,760 --> 00:01:20,079
Oh, I stepped out to handle something.

5
00:01:20,079 --> 00:01:21,319
I'm in a taxi right now.

6
00:01:22,079 --> 00:01:23,000
I'll be at the bank shortly.

7
00:01:24,719 --> 00:01:26,799
Come to my office as soon as you're back.

8
00:01:27,879 --> 00:01:29,280
The Economic Crimes Unit is here.

9
00:01:29,560 --> 00:01:30,640
They've come to ask about something.

10
00:01:46,319 --> 00:01:47,040
Twenty-six.

11
00:01:49,560 --> 00:01:50,879
Ma'am, we're here.

12
00:01:50,879 --> 00:01:51,319
Oh.

13
00:01:51,319 --> 00:01:51,959
Twenty-six.

14
00:02:06,719 --> 00:02:09,280
I'd driven her a few times before.

15
00:02:09,680 --> 00:02:11,240
I knew she worked at a bank.

16
00:02:11,599 --> 00:02:14,159
At the time, I meant to return the keys to her.

17
00:02:14,560 --> 00:02:15,280
Go on.

18
00:02:17,360 --> 00:02:17,879
I...

19
00:02:18,240 --> 00:02:19,960
I've told you everything I know.

20
00:02:20,560 --> 00:02:21,599
I've laid it all out for you.

21
00:02:21,599 --> 00:02:23,199
This counts as turning myself in, right?

22
00:02:23,639 --> 00:02:24,759
As long as you hide nothing

23
00:02:24,759 --> 00:02:26,439
and tell the truth, it counts.

24
00:02:29,680 --> 00:02:32,199
I knew she had quite a bit of money.

25
00:02:32,199 --> 00:02:34,159
And I knew that necklace had to be valuable.

26
00:02:34,439 --> 00:02:35,960
But I really had no idea that necklace

27
00:02:35,960 --> 00:02:37,280
could be worth over a million.

28
00:02:38,919 --> 00:02:40,039
You guys must know already

29
00:02:40,360 --> 00:02:42,000
I have a lot of gambling debts.

30
00:02:42,360 --> 00:02:43,039
I know...

31
00:02:43,199 --> 00:02:45,199
This was a chance for me to pay it off.

32
00:02:47,159 --> 00:02:49,319
So I secretly made a copy of the key.

33
00:02:49,479 --> 00:02:51,400
After copying it, I returned her key.

34
00:02:52,240 --> 00:02:53,719
The day I gave her keys back,

35
00:02:54,159 --> 00:02:56,000
she didn't seem to be doing too well.

36
00:02:56,919 --> 00:02:58,199
But she was still really nice.

37
00:02:58,199 --> 00:02:59,879
She even gave me 200 yuan as a thank-you.

38
00:03:00,879 --> 00:03:01,439
Sir.

39
00:03:01,680 --> 00:03:03,240
The Economic Crimes Unit must've been onto her.

40
00:03:03,360 --> 00:03:05,000
In her panic, she left the keys in the cab.

41
00:03:05,719 --> 00:03:06,840
The night Shen Qing fell to her death,

42
00:03:06,840 --> 00:03:07,800
what happened at her place?

43
00:03:08,479 --> 00:03:09,520
That night,

44
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:11,840
I just went to her place to steal stuff.

45
00:03:12,520 --> 00:03:15,639
I went to Yunhai Bathhouse first.

46
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:17,560
Because I'd cased the place before.

47
00:03:17,560 --> 00:03:19,680
I knew that spot was pretty close to her place.

48
00:03:40,719 --> 00:03:42,199
Why are you looking at me like that?

49
00:03:42,199 --> 00:03:44,319
I... I've told you everything I know.

50
00:03:44,520 --> 00:03:45,840
Did you get a clear look at his face?

51
00:03:46,719 --> 00:03:47,560
It was dark.

52
00:03:48,400 --> 00:03:50,280
He had a mask on. I couldn't see.

53
00:03:51,599 --> 00:03:53,400
But after Shen Qing left,

54
00:03:53,840 --> 00:03:55,680
the man in black went back in.

55
00:03:56,639 --> 00:03:57,919
When he left,

56
00:03:58,919 --> 00:03:59,800
I think

57
00:04:00,400 --> 00:04:01,840
he took a laptop with him.

58
00:04:14,159 --> 00:04:15,479
I was afraid of making too much noise,

59
00:04:15,639 --> 00:04:16,680
that the neighbors would call the cops.

60
00:04:17,439 --> 00:04:19,240
So I wrote a note to scare them.

61
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:28,800
And then?

62
00:04:29,680 --> 00:04:30,480
Then

63
00:04:31,439 --> 00:04:32,279
I went inside

64
00:04:32,920 --> 00:04:33,879
and took the necklace.

65
00:04:47,040 --> 00:04:47,920
You didn't steal anything else?

66
00:04:48,959 --> 00:04:49,959
I only took the necklace.

67
00:04:49,959 --> 00:04:51,120
I didn't touch anything else.

68
00:04:51,800 --> 00:04:53,079
I really didn't.

69
00:04:54,199 --> 00:04:55,920
Then this whole confession was useless.

70
00:04:56,120 --> 00:04:57,279
You didn't see the man's face.

71
00:04:57,439 --> 00:04:58,600
You don't know how Shen Qing died.

72
00:04:58,879 --> 00:04:59,959
You call this turning yourself in?

73
00:05:01,240 --> 00:05:02,560
But everything I know,

74
00:05:02,560 --> 00:05:04,160
I've already told you.

75
00:05:06,920 --> 00:05:08,360
A blind man lighting a candle—total waste.

76
00:05:08,560 --> 00:05:09,879
Sir, the way I see it,

77
00:05:10,120 --> 00:05:11,160
just send him to detention.

78
00:05:12,240 --> 00:05:12,920
He's said all he's got.

79
00:05:15,120 --> 00:05:16,879
Call the team now. Send him to detention.

80
00:05:17,079 --> 00:05:17,639
Right.

81
00:05:17,839 --> 00:05:18,720
Officer Jiang.

82
00:05:19,600 --> 00:05:20,600
Brother Hu is badly injured.

83
00:05:20,720 --> 00:05:22,000
Let him recover for a few days first.

84
00:05:22,399 --> 00:05:23,600
We already gave him a chance.

85
00:05:23,720 --> 00:05:24,959
If he blew it, that's on him.

86
00:05:25,920 --> 00:05:27,519
Xiao Hu, it's come to this point.

87
00:05:27,519 --> 00:05:28,639
What are you still hiding?

88
00:05:30,560 --> 00:05:32,279
No cash in Shen Qing's drawers, right?

89
00:05:32,439 --> 00:05:33,000
There was.

90
00:05:37,079 --> 00:05:39,839
Didn't you say you didn't touch anything else?

91
00:05:40,920 --> 00:05:42,800
I, I, I...

92
00:05:45,600 --> 00:05:46,800
I only took the necklace.

93
00:05:47,199 --> 00:05:48,879
The cash and other jewelry I didn't touch.

94
00:05:48,879 --> 00:05:49,959
Can you make that story add up?

95
00:05:50,079 --> 00:05:51,279
I... I...

96
00:05:51,279 --> 00:05:52,639
What actually happened?

97
00:05:53,480 --> 00:05:55,040
Later I found out Shen Qing was dead.

98
00:05:55,040 --> 00:05:57,879
I... I was scared.

99
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:02,680
I...

100
00:06:03,279 --> 00:06:04,279
I remember now.

101
00:06:05,319 --> 00:06:06,519
That night,

102
00:06:08,920 --> 00:06:10,199
at Shen Qing's place,

103
00:06:11,319 --> 00:06:13,519
I did see another man.

104
00:06:16,160 --> 00:06:17,600
Through a gap in the curtains,

105
00:06:19,480 --> 00:06:21,560
I secretly took a few photos.

106
00:06:24,480 --> 00:06:26,399
The man cleaning up at her place

107
00:06:27,480 --> 00:06:29,120
was the president of Fengdu Bank,

108
00:06:29,720 --> 00:06:30,680
Su Zhuang.

109
00:07:46,839 --> 00:07:47,519
Mengmeng,

110
00:07:48,519 --> 00:07:49,680
Thanks for putting in a good word.

111
00:07:50,279 --> 00:07:52,079
President Xu finally agreed to see me.

112
00:07:52,639 --> 00:07:55,199
Brother Su, there's no need to be so polite.

113
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:57,759
President Xu has truly been swamped lately.

114
00:07:57,959 --> 00:08:00,360
The moment she had time, she had me invite you.

115
00:08:02,560 --> 00:08:03,240
Come in.

116
00:08:09,079 --> 00:08:09,680
Sister Wen.

117
00:08:10,160 --> 00:08:10,720
You're here.

118
00:08:10,879 --> 00:08:11,399
Yes.

119
00:08:11,600 --> 00:08:12,240
Have a seat.

120
00:08:17,279 --> 00:08:18,079
Did you drive here?

121
00:08:19,240 --> 00:08:20,920
When do you ever not drive here?

122
00:08:23,319 --> 00:08:24,639
But this time is different.

123
00:08:26,040 --> 00:08:27,399
Are you in some kind of trouble?

124
00:08:27,759 --> 00:08:28,839
So you've already heard.

125
00:08:30,600 --> 00:08:33,279
About your credit chief falling to his death?

126
00:08:33,639 --> 00:08:36,080
In Fengdu, who doesn't know?

127
00:08:38,440 --> 00:08:39,120
Sister Wen.

128
00:08:40,279 --> 00:08:41,600
I won't beat around the bush.

129
00:08:42,320 --> 00:08:43,399
Shen Qing's death,

130
00:08:43,679 --> 00:08:44,960
what exactly happened?

131
00:08:45,799 --> 00:08:46,639
President Su,

132
00:08:47,639 --> 00:08:49,840
if the police heard you say that,

133
00:08:50,080 --> 00:08:52,159
wouldn't I get dragged into this too?

134
00:08:52,679 --> 00:08:54,879
But the police are already on to me.

135
00:08:56,320 --> 00:08:57,919
We've worked together for years,

136
00:08:58,440 --> 00:08:59,840
and you're still not being honest.

137
00:09:00,879 --> 00:09:04,240
Are you saying Shen Qing's death really has nothing to do with you?

138
00:09:05,720 --> 00:09:06,360
Sister Wen,

139
00:09:06,919 --> 00:09:09,000
I was just solving a problem for both of us.

140
00:09:09,080 --> 00:09:09,720
Oh.

141
00:09:10,320 --> 00:09:11,639
Well, since the problem is solved,

142
00:09:11,720 --> 00:09:12,759
what are you worrying about?

143
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:14,639
But I really didn't kill Shen Qing.

144
00:09:14,759 --> 00:09:17,080
I have no idea how Shen Qing actually died.

145
00:09:17,320 --> 00:09:18,759
Then you're asking the wrong person.

146
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:20,759
You should ask the police.

147
00:09:21,120 --> 00:09:23,159
The police suspect I killed her.

148
00:09:24,120 --> 00:09:25,519
Well, since you didn't do it,

149
00:09:25,879 --> 00:09:28,399
that proves Shen Qing committed suicide, right?

150
00:09:29,399 --> 00:09:30,240
Suicide?

151
00:09:31,240 --> 00:09:32,639
Did Shen Qing really kill herself?

152
00:09:35,360 --> 00:09:36,440
If it wasn't suicide,

153
00:09:37,240 --> 00:09:38,559
then who do you think killed her?

154
00:09:42,919 --> 00:09:43,559
Sister Wen,

155
00:09:45,840 --> 00:09:46,519
was it you?

156
00:09:47,279 --> 00:09:49,799
I don't care whether you killed Shen Qing.

157
00:09:50,399 --> 00:09:53,240
And I don't care how you explain it to the police.

158
00:09:54,360 --> 00:09:55,679
But you must remember one thing.

159
00:09:56,039 --> 00:09:57,559
If you drag me into this,

160
00:09:58,039 --> 00:10:00,440
then I truly won't be able to help you.

161
00:10:02,240 --> 00:10:03,039
Sister Wen,

162
00:10:04,279 --> 00:10:05,559
you really can help me.

163
00:10:07,360 --> 00:10:08,799
You help me, I help you.

164
00:10:08,960 --> 00:10:10,240
After all these years,

165
00:10:10,879 --> 00:10:12,120
now that you're in trouble,

166
00:10:12,600 --> 00:10:15,120
of course I'll do everything I can to help.

167
00:10:20,480 --> 00:10:21,519
Thank you, Sister Wen.

168
00:10:22,320 --> 00:10:24,440
But heed my advice.

169
00:10:24,840 --> 00:10:27,200
Don't get too greedy for power and money.

170
00:10:27,679 --> 00:10:28,480
It's time

171
00:10:29,039 --> 00:10:30,120
to step back.

172
00:10:31,480 --> 00:10:32,080
Understood.

173
00:10:33,919 --> 00:10:35,200
The paperwork to leave the country

174
00:10:36,559 --> 00:10:37,600
is already being processed.

175
00:10:38,600 --> 00:10:39,480
That's more like it.

176
00:11:07,159 --> 00:11:08,960
We're officers from the Fengdu Major Crimes Unit.

177
00:11:09,679 --> 00:11:11,799
Per the Criminal Procedure Law,

178
00:11:11,960 --> 00:11:13,360
you are hereby placed under criminal detention.

179
00:11:13,799 --> 00:11:14,679
Here's the detention warrant.

180
00:11:15,759 --> 00:11:16,320
Captain Li,

181
00:11:17,320 --> 00:11:19,159
there must be some misunderstanding.

182
00:11:19,720 --> 00:11:20,360
Cuff him.

183
00:11:23,919 --> 00:11:24,639
I guarantee you,

184
00:11:25,120 --> 00:11:26,039
within three days,

185
00:11:26,480 --> 00:11:28,039
you'll have to release me.

186
00:11:29,480 --> 00:11:30,080
Take him away.

187
00:11:35,759 --> 00:11:36,399
Wrap it up.

188
00:11:42,720 --> 00:11:43,879
I'll ask you one last time.

189
00:11:44,559 --> 00:11:46,279
Where were you on the night of the 23rd?

190
00:11:48,879 --> 00:11:51,000
Then I'll answer you one last time.

191
00:11:52,159 --> 00:11:53,759
I got home around 9:30.

192
00:11:54,440 --> 00:11:55,159
The whole night,

193
00:11:55,759 --> 00:11:56,879
I never went out.

194
00:11:57,679 --> 00:11:58,759
Think carefully before you answer.

195
00:11:59,600 --> 00:12:02,120
Would we detain you without solid evidence?

196
00:12:07,679 --> 00:12:09,360
President Su, ever worked as a cleaner?

197
00:12:15,519 --> 00:12:16,799
I don't mean to mock you.

198
00:12:17,559 --> 00:12:19,799
I just think your cleaning work was

199
00:12:19,799 --> 00:12:21,320
both professional and swift.

200
00:12:22,639 --> 00:12:23,919
Not a single trace left behind.

201
00:12:23,919 --> 00:12:25,600
Not even a strand of hair.

202
00:12:25,919 --> 00:12:26,840
I'm curious—

203
00:12:28,039 --> 00:12:29,120
how did you manage it?

204
00:12:30,679 --> 00:12:32,759
Captain Li, if you like joking around,

205
00:12:34,399 --> 00:12:36,360
let's meet up another time, just us.

206
00:12:37,360 --> 00:12:39,480
I'll take you out to let loose.

207
00:12:41,600 --> 00:12:43,120
You think I'm bluffing, right?

208
00:12:45,840 --> 00:12:47,480
Didn't you clean Shen Qing's place?

209
00:12:54,639 --> 00:12:56,399
Oh, Captain Li,

210
00:12:57,720 --> 00:12:59,559
you really are a master joker.

211
00:13:04,879 --> 00:13:07,039
Shen Qing was just an ordinary colleague.

212
00:13:07,559 --> 00:13:09,360
How could I be at her place?

213
00:13:10,039 --> 00:13:10,960
Secondly,

214
00:13:12,080 --> 00:13:13,720
that night I was home the entire time.

215
00:13:14,639 --> 00:13:17,399
How could I have been anywhere else?

216
00:13:17,759 --> 00:13:19,840
Hey, did I say I cleaned anything that night?

217
00:13:20,200 --> 00:13:21,639
I assure you, absolutely not.

218
00:13:21,720 --> 00:13:22,320
Oh.

219
00:13:23,039 --> 00:13:24,440
But President Su, you seem to

220
00:13:24,440 --> 00:13:26,240
remember that night quite clearly.

221
00:13:27,440 --> 00:13:28,799
Care to elaborate?

222
00:13:34,120 --> 00:13:35,720
You just said two "impossibles."

223
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:37,759
So let me ask you—

224
00:13:38,879 --> 00:13:41,559
why was your clothing found at Shen Qing's home?

225
00:13:43,960 --> 00:13:44,679
Clothing?

226
00:13:45,360 --> 00:13:46,279
What clothing?

227
00:13:48,960 --> 00:13:50,399
Is this how you cops handle cases?

228
00:13:51,399 --> 00:13:52,320
Just like this?

229
00:13:52,720 --> 00:13:53,639
Without any evidence?

230
00:13:55,399 --> 00:13:56,799
I was home all night that day.

231
00:13:56,799 --> 00:13:58,679
Hasn't my wife already confirmed that?

232
00:13:59,480 --> 00:14:00,039
Fine.

233
00:14:00,360 --> 00:14:01,559
Let me help refresh your memory.

234
00:14:03,320 --> 00:14:05,039
According to your wife's statement,

235
00:14:05,960 --> 00:14:07,600
that night, you arrived home

236
00:14:08,279 --> 00:14:09,320
at around 9:30.

237
00:14:10,200 --> 00:14:12,279
Then you started dinner around 9:50.

238
00:14:12,919 --> 00:14:13,759
Key detail—

239
00:14:14,799 --> 00:14:16,960
you personally poured two glasses of wine

240
00:14:18,200 --> 00:14:19,440
and gave one to your wife.

241
00:14:20,440 --> 00:14:21,519
My description is accurate, right?

242
00:14:30,360 --> 00:14:32,320
Is it illegal for a couple to drink at home?

243
00:14:34,840 --> 00:14:35,759
What I mean is,

244
00:14:36,519 --> 00:14:38,039
it shows your love for each other.

245
00:14:39,080 --> 00:14:40,360
But this love—

246
00:14:41,039 --> 00:14:42,039
it was a little too intense.

247
00:14:42,600 --> 00:14:43,440
Come on, bottoms up.

248
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:53,480
After your wife finished her drink,

249
00:14:53,840 --> 00:14:55,080
she quickly got drunk.

250
00:14:58,080 --> 00:14:59,440
What are you trying to say?

251
00:14:59,879 --> 00:15:02,559
After helping your drunk wife to the bedroom,

252
00:15:03,559 --> 00:15:05,000
you quickly returned to the living room,

253
00:15:06,120 --> 00:15:08,200
because you were waiting for an important call.

254
00:15:31,679 --> 00:15:32,519
Hello, Godfather.

255
00:15:32,519 --> 00:15:33,320
How did it go?

256
00:15:34,080 --> 00:15:34,919
I got the laptop.

257
00:15:35,840 --> 00:15:36,679
She said there's no backup.

258
00:15:37,559 --> 00:15:38,519
She didn't seem to be lying.

259
00:15:39,919 --> 00:15:41,399
Nothing went wrong, right?

260
00:15:42,200 --> 00:15:42,879
Don't worry.

261
00:15:43,600 --> 00:15:45,120
But she ran off.

262
00:15:47,399 --> 00:15:48,080
Got it.

263
00:15:48,480 --> 00:15:49,320
Get out of there now.

264
00:15:53,679 --> 00:15:55,159
You cops...

265
00:15:56,600 --> 00:15:58,399
really are masters at making up stories.

266
00:15:58,840 --> 00:16:00,320
What era are we living in?

267
00:16:00,600 --> 00:16:02,720
Still pulling these baseless accusations?

268
00:16:02,720 --> 00:16:04,000
President Su, take it easy.

269
00:16:05,360 --> 00:16:06,519
Just treat it as a story.

270
00:16:08,960 --> 00:16:10,240
You said that day

271
00:16:10,919 --> 00:16:11,720
you didn't go out.

272
00:16:12,399 --> 00:16:13,559
Your wife can vouch for that.

273
00:16:14,679 --> 00:16:16,279
But your wife was asleep.

274
00:16:16,879 --> 00:16:17,840
So who can vouch for you?

275
00:16:19,639 --> 00:16:21,240
She only slept for twenty minutes.

276
00:16:22,639 --> 00:16:24,120
In such a short time,

277
00:16:24,559 --> 00:16:25,399
what could I possibly do?

278
00:16:25,559 --> 00:16:26,559
Could I fly?

279
00:16:31,679 --> 00:16:32,440
This alarm clock

280
00:16:33,519 --> 00:16:34,720
is the same as the one in your home, right?

281
00:16:36,039 --> 00:16:37,159
Let me give you a demonstration.

282
00:17:18,160 --> 00:17:20,039
Quite the captivating story.

283
